{"title_page": "1974\u201375 Juventus F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club = Juventus Football Club\n|season = 1974-75\n|manager = [[Carlo Parola]]\n|chairman = [[Giampiero Boniperti]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1974-75 Serie A|1st]] <br>(in [[1975-76 European Cup|European Cup]])\n|cup1 = [[Coppa Italia]]\n|cup1 result = [[1974-75 Coppa Italia|Second round]]\n|cup2 = [[UEFA Cup]]\n|cup2 result = [[1974-75 UEFA Cup|Semifinals]]\n|league topscorer = [[Oscar Damiani|Damiani]] (9)\n|season topscorer = [[Pietro Anastasi]] (21)\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Comunale]]\n|average attendance = {{formatnum:41820}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stadiapostcards.com/a2.htm.htm|title=Attendance Statistics of Serie A - 1974-75 to 1985-86}}</ref>\n\n|pattern_la1 =_juve80sh\n|leftarm1 = ffffff\n|pattern_b1 =_juve196972h\n|body1 = ffffff\n|pattern_ra1 =_juve80sh\n|rightarm1 = ffffff\n|shorts1 = ffffff\n|pattern_so1 =_juve3\n|socks1 = 000000\n\n|pattern_la2 =_juve7081a\n|leftarm2 = 002657\n|pattern_b2 =_juve7071a\n|body2 = 002657\n|pattern_ra2 =_juve7081a\n|rightarm2 = 002657\n|shorts2 = 002657\n|pattern_so2 =\n|socks2 = 002657\n\n|prevseason = [[1973-74 Juventus F.C. season|1973-74]]\n|nextseason = [[1975-76 Juventus F.C. season|1975-76]]\n}}\n\nDuring 1974/75 season Juventus competed in Serie A, Coppa Italia and UEFA Cup.\n\n== Summary ==\nCarlo Parola returned to the team after 12 years <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttojuve.com/gli-eroi-bianconeri/gli-eroi-in-bianconero-carlo-parola-63346|title=Gli eroi in bianconero: Carlo PAROLA|publisher=Tutto Juve|language=Italian|author1=Stefano Bedeschi|date=20 September 2013|accessdate=31 March 2016}}</ref> along with new arrivals Damiani and Scirea. Anastasi became the new captain after the retirement of Sandro Salvadore.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,9/articleid,1501_02_1974_0175_0009_21168181/|title=Anastasi impara a parlare da capitano|publisher=Stampa Sera|author=Franco Costa|date=6 August 1974|p=9|language=Italian}}</ref> A reinforced Juventus clinched its 16th league against runners-up Napoli.\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Giancarlo Alessandrelli]] | pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Massimo Piloni]] |pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Dino Zoff]] |pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Antonello Cuccureddu]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Claudio Gentile]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Silvio Longobucco]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Francesco Morini]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Gaetano Scirea]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Luciano Spinosi]] |pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Franco Causio]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Fabio Capello]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Damiani]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Furino]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Alberto Marchetti]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Fernando Viola]] |pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=BRA|name= [[Jos\u00e9 Altafini]] |pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Pietro Anastasi]] |pos=FW}}(captain)\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name=[[Roberto Bettega]] |pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no= |nat=ITA|name= [[Paolo Rossi]] |pos=FW}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1974-75 Serie A}}\n\n====League table====\n{{:1974-75 Serie A|showteam=JUV}}\n\n==== Matches====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 6 October 1974\n|time = \n|round = 1\n|team1 = [[Bologna F.C.|Bologna]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 2-1\n|report = http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1974/12281/\n|location = [[Bologna]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Renato Dall'Ara|Comunale]]\n|attendance = \n|referee = [[Riccardo Lattanzi|R. Lattanzi]]\n|goals1 = [[Giuseppe Savoldi|G. Savoldi]] {{Goal|21}}<br/>