{"title_page": "1975\u201376 A.C. Torino season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club = [[Torino F.C.|Associazione Calcio Torino]]\n|season = 1975\u201376\n|manager = [[Luigi Radice]]\n|chairman = Orfeo Pianelli\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1975\u201376 Serie A|1st]]<br> (in [[1976-77 European Cup|European Cup]])\n|cup1 = [[Coppa Italia]]\n|cup1 result = [[1975\u201376 Coppa Italia|First round]]\n|league topscorer = [[Paolino Pulici|Pulici]] (21)\n|season topscorer = [[Paolino Pulici|Pulici]] (23)\n|highest attendance = {{formatnum:64733}} vs Cesena <br>(16 May 1976)\n|lowest attendance = {{formatnum:11599}} vs Novara <br>(14 September 1975)\n|average attendance = {{formatnum:39145}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stadiapostcards.com/a2.htm.htm|title=Attendance Statistics of Serie A \u2013 1974-75 to 1985-86|publisher=stadiapostcards.com}}</ref>\n\n|pattern_la1 = \n|leftarm1 = 831d1c\n|pattern_b1 = \n|body1 = 831d1c\n|pattern_ra1 = \n|rightarm1 = 831d1c\n|shorts1 = 831d1c\n|socks1 = 831d1c\n|title1 = Home\n\n|pattern_b2 = \n|body2 = ffffff\n|pattern_la2 = _borderonwhite\n|leftarm2 = 831d1c\n|pattern_ra2 = _borderonwhite\n|rightarm2 = 831d1c\n|shorts2 = 831d1c\n|socks2 = 831d1c\n|title2 = Away\n\n|prevseason = [[1974-75 Torino F.C.|1974-75]]\n|nextseason = [[1976-77 Torino F.C.|1976-77]]\n}}\nIn the 1975\u201376 Associazione Calcio Torino competed in Serie A and Coppa Italia.\n==Summary==\nThe team placed first being their seventh Serie A title in the 1975\u201376 season. The scudetto was won after a comeback against [[Juventus]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Luciano Castellini|url=http://www.dnamilan.com/nemici-storici/luciano-castellini.html|accessdate=3 January 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103090342/http://www.dnamilan.com/nemici-storici/luciano-castellini.html|archivedate=3 January 2015}}</ref>, who held a five-point advantage over the Granata during the spring. However, three straight losses for the Bianconeri, the second of which was in the derby, allowed [[Torino]] to overtake.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://storiedicalcio.altervista.org/blog/torino_75_76.html|title=season 75/76 Toro|language=IT}}</ref> In the final round, Torino held a one-point advantage and, until then, had won every previous home fixture. Torino hosted Cesena at the Comunale but could only manage to draw; Juventus, however, were defeated at Perugia<ref>{{cite web |url=http://torinofc.it/en/contenuto-storia/1975-1976-torino-won-championship|title=1975-1976: Torino won the championship|publisher=torinofc.it|access-date=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n. The title was won by two points ahead of Juventus, 27 years after the Superga tragedy.\n\n==Squad==\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosa Torino 75/76|url=http://calcio-seriea.net/rose/1975/757/|publisher=calcio-seriea.net|access-date=2 January 2020|language=Italian}}</ref>\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luciano Castellini]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Romano Cazzaniga]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mauro Pelosin]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Vittorio Caporale]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Fabrizio Gorin]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Marino Lombardo]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Roberto Mozzini]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Pallavicini]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Roberto Salvadori]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Nello Santin]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Roberto Bacchin]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Eraldo Pecci]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Roccotelli]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Claudio Sala]]|pos=MF}}([[Captain (association football)|Captain]])\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Patrizio Sala]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Renato Zaccarelli]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Marzio Bertocchi]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Salvatore Garritano]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Francesco Graziani]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Paolino Pulici]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs end}}\n===Transfers===\n<div style=\"float: left; width: 50%;\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;width:99%;\"\n\n! colspan=\"4\" | In\n|-\n! width=3% | Pos.\n! width=32% | Name\n! width=30% | from\n! width=35% | Cost\n|-\n| GK || [[Romano Cazzaniga]] || Taranto || Released\n|-\n| GK || [[Claudio Garella]] || Juniorcasale || loan ended\n|-\n| DF || [[Paolo Beruatto]] || Ivrea || loan ended\n|-\n| DF || [[Vittorio Caporale]] || [[Bologna F.C.|Bologna]] ||  (U$ 0.158 million)\n|-\n| DF || [[Fabrizio Gorin]] || [[Vicenza Calcio|Lanerossi]] ||  (U$ 0.539 million)\n|-\n| MF || [[Roberto Bacchin]] || Rimini || \n|-\n| MF || [[Eraldo Pecci]] || [[Bologna F.C.|Bologna]] || (U$ 1.111 million)\n|-\n| MF || [[Patrizio Sala]] || [[A.C. Monza]] || (U$ 0.365 million)\n|-\n| FW || [[Salvatore Garritano]] || Ternana || (U$ 1.111 million)\n|}\n</div>\n<div style=\"float: left; width: 50%;\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;width:99%;\"\n\n! colspan=\"4\" | Out\n|-\n! width=3% | Pos.\n! width=32% | Name\n! width=30% | to\n! width=35% | Type\n|-\n| GK || [[Claudio Garella]] || Novara || loan\n|-\n| GK || [[Giuliano Manfredi]] || Modena || released\n|-\n| GK || [[Antonio Pigino]] || Sambenedettese || released\n|-\n| GK || [[Franco Sattolo]] || || retire\n|-\n| DF || [[Paolo Beruatto]] || [[A.C. Monza]] || released\n|-\n| DF || [[Vito Callioni]] || [[Vicenza Calcio|Lanerossi]] || released\n|-\n| DF || [[Angelo Cereser]] || [[Bologna F.C.|Bologna]] || released\n|-\n| MF || [[Aldo Agroppi]] || [[A.C. Perugia|Perugia]] || released\n|-\n| MF || [[Giorgio Ferrini]] || || retire\n|-\n| MF || [[Emiliano Mascetti]] || [[Hellas Verona]] || released\n|-\n| FW || [[Pierantonio Bortot]] || Cremonese || released\n|-\n| FW || [[Giovanni Quadri]] || Pistoiese || loan\n|-\n| FW || [[Ferdinando Rossi]] || Avellino || released\n|}\