 with a resolution of 480x854 with 196 ppi. It is powered by a 1&nbsp;GHz dual-core CPU, 512MB of RAM and runs on Android 4.0.4 ICS(Upgradable to Android 4.1.1).  The device has 4 GB internal storage of which 1.05 GB is user available that can be expanded up to 32GB via a microSD or mircroSDHC card. The rear of the Micromax Canvas 2 A110 has an 8MP camera with dual LED flash and the front has 0.3MP VGA camera for video-calling. The Micromax Canvas 2 A110 comes with preloaded apps such as M!Buddy, CricketFever, HookUp, Micromax MZone and the Micromax MStore. \n\nOfficial Jelly Bean update for Micromax A110 Canvas 2 has been announced, [http://www.techzooo.com/jelly-bean-update-micromax-a110-canvas-2-announced/ Details].\n\n==Hardware==\nMicromax A110 Canvas 2 is powered by 1&nbsp;GHz ARM Dual-Core Cortex A9 processor on  MediaTek's MT6577 SoC with PowerVR SGX531 GPU.<ref>http://www.mobilephonenews.org/micromax-a110-full-review/</ref> It has 512 MB RAM.<ref>http://techwayz.com/micromax-canvas-2-price-specifications/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n https://web.archive.org/web/20140111094554/http://micromax-phones.com/mobile/micromax-canvas-2-a110-2/\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Smartphones]]\n[[Category:Micromax Mobile]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2012]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|Products|date=May 2013}}\n{{refimprove |date=May 2013}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name = Micromax Canvas 2 A110<ref>{{cite news | url=http://micromaxcanvas.co.in/micromax-canvas-2-plus-a110q-price-specification-details/ | publisher=Micromax | title=Everything you need to know about canvas 2 | access-date=18 June 2013 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206131910/http://micromaxcanvas.co.in/micromax-canvas-2-plus-a110q-price-specification-details/ | archive-date=6 December 2017 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| image = \n| i